The Governor of Kogi State, Mr Yahaya Bello, on Thursday inaugurated the state electoral body. He said the state was set to conduct elections in to the 21 local government areas with the inauguration of the State Independent Electoral Commission. The commission, headed by Maman Eri, was inaugurated alongside the state Judicial Service Commission headed by the Chief Judge, Justice Nasir Ajana. The governor urged the electoral commission to set machinery in motion by coming up with a timetable that would be acceptable and fair to all and within reasonable timeframe as stipulated by law. “In discharging your duties, you must study all relevant laws and be guided accordingly. You must be fair, just and you should not look at the face of anybody and you should be guided by the law while discharging your duties,”Bello said. The governor also charged the judicial service commission to continue on the path of righteousness which the judiciary was noted for. Bello announced the appointment of Senior Special Assistant on Security in each of the 21 local government areas of the state. The newly appointed SSAs on security are to be in charge of security matters in the local government areas and report directly to the governor. Copyright PUNCH.
